{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:hebrews.3",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "hebrews",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Hebrews 3 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:1",
      "text": "Therefore, holy brothers, partakers of a heavenly calling, consider the Apostle and High Priest of our confession: Jesus,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:2",
      "text": "who was faithful to him who appointed him, as also Moses was in all his house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:3",
      "text": "For he has been counted worthy of more glory than Moses, because he who built the house has more honor than the house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:4",
      "text": "For every house is built by someone; but he who built all things is God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:5",
      "text": "Moses indeed was faithful in all his house as a servant, for a testimony of those things which were afterward to be spoken,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:6",
      "text": "but Christ is faithful as a Son over his house. We are his house, if we hold fast our confidence and the glorying of our hope firm to the end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:7",
      "text": "Therefore, even as the Holy Spirit says, “ Today if you will hear his voice,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:8",
      "text": "don’ t harden your hearts as in the rebellion, in the day of the trial in the wilderness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:9",
      "text": "where your fathers tested me and tried me, and saw my deeds for forty years.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:10",
      "text": "Therefore I was displeased with that generation, and said, ‘ They always err in their heart, but they didn’ t know my ways.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:11",
      "text": "As I swore in my wrath, ‘ They will not enter into my rest.’”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:12",
      "text": "Beware, brothers, lest perhaps there might be in any one of you an evil heart of unbelief, in falling away from the living God;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:13",
      "text": "but exhort one another day by day, so long as it is called “ today ”, lest any one of you be hardened by the deceitfulness of sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:14",
      "text": "For we have become partakers of Christ, if we hold the beginning of our confidence firm to the end,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:15",
      "text": "while it is said, “ Today if you will hear his voice, don’ t harden your hearts, as in the rebellion.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:16",
      "text": "For who, when they heard, rebelled? Wasn’ t it all those who came out of Egypt led by Moses?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:17",
      "text": "With whom was he displeased forty years? Wasn’ t it with those who sinned, whose bodies fell in the wilderness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:18",
      "text": "To whom did he swear that they wouldn’ t enter into his rest, but to those who were disobedient?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:hebrews.3.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "hebrews",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Hebrews 3:19",
      "text": "We see that they weren’t able to enter in because of unbelief.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
